---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const url = (p: string) => `${base.replace(/\/$/, "")}/${p.replace(/^\//, "")}`;
---
<BaseLayout title="OpenIT — your IT helpdesk, in plain English">
  <h1>Your IT helpdesk, in plain English.</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    OpenIT is a small desktop app that wraps Claude Code with the chrome an IT
    admin needs — a project explorer, a viewer, a chat-intake URL for askers,
    and bidirectional sync with your Pinkfish cloud workspace. Describe what
    you want; Claude writes it as files in your repo. Hit sync and the same
    files run in production.
  </p>

  <div class="cta-row">
    <a href={url("/download")} class="btn">
      Download for macOS
      <span class="sub">Beta &middot; Apple Silicon + Intel</span>
    </a>
    <a href="https://github.com/pinkfish-ai/openit-app" class="btn secondary">View on GitHub</a>
  </div>

  <h2>What it is</h2>
  <p>
    A Tauri shell that pins a Claude Code session to a project folder. The
    OpenIT plugin (skills, schemas, MCPs, scripts) is bundled in, so Claude
    knows the helpdesk shape from the first turn — tickets, knowledge bases,
    people, agents, files, reports.
  </p>
  <p>
    Everything Claude writes is plain Markdown and JSON in a directory you
    control. No proprietary database. No clicky admin UI. No paid sandbox to
    "test" against.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Open a project.</strong> OpenIT scaffolds a clean directory —
      <code>databases/</code>, <code>knowledge-bases/</code>, <code>agents/</code>,
      <code>filestores/</code> — and starts a local chat-intake URL so askers
      can file tickets immediately.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Connect to Pinkfish (optional).</strong> Two-click browser OAuth.
      Your org's datastores, KB articles, agents, and files sync into the local
      repo. Local-only mode also works — it's a real helpdesk on your laptop.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Talk to Claude.</strong> <em>"Add a KB article for password resets."</em>
      <em>"Tighten the triage agent so it tags tickets by topic."</em>
      <em>"Show me last week's escalations grouped by asker."</em> Claude reads
      the files, edits them, writes new ones — you see the diffs in the viewer.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Sync.</strong> Local edits push to Pinkfish on save; cloud changes
      pull on connect. Slack ingest, channel webhooks, multi-device — all light
      up the moment cloud is connected.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Why files on disk</h2>
  <p>
    ITSM as code, in git. Diffs you can read. PRs you can review. Branches for
    staging vs prod. Rollback by <code>git revert</code>. Edit in any editor.
    Hand the repo to your terminal-native engineers and they're productive
    immediately — every file OpenIT writes is identical to what plain Claude
    Code would write. If you ever leave OpenIT, you take your config with you.
  </p>

  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
  <p>
    IT admins at small and mid-sized companies who want Pinkfish-grade
    automation without spinning up a platform team. If you can describe what
    you need in a Slack message, you can build it in OpenIT.
  </p>

  <h2>Status</h2>
  <p>
    Public beta. macOS only (Apple Silicon + Intel), signed and notarized — no
    Gatekeeper warning on first launch. Linux and Windows builds follow.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
